RHS/MS Families‚ÄîWe had a good first day of school today. It was so nice to have kids back in our building even if there are some different ways we have to do business. Our students were awesome just as I would have expected them to be. Parents‚Äî thank you for preparing them to be flexible and patient as we work through the kinks of starting a new school year. Please contact me if there questions or concerns that we can work on to make each day better for our students!

I would also like to thank our staff. Teachers, bus drivers, cooks, paras, and office staff took the challenges of starting school in stride and have done a tremendous job getting prepared to get the school year off the ground!

Joel Swenson
RHS/MS Principal

post_text:
Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.

Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

Families may qualify for additional funds to purchase nutritious food. Families with children ages 5 to 18 who qualified for free or reduced-price school meals, but not SNAP or MFIP, are urged to apply at www.mn.p-ebt.org or contact the P-EBT hotline to find out more: 651-431-4050 or 800-657-3698.

post_text:
Hello families!! Becker Screen Printing & Design in Pierz MN has worked with our schools for over 7 years. They use their dollar to stock our Lions Den Store, and their time to staff the store. They are contributors to our sports, clubs, and organizations. They are useful to our school community as they provide a valuable service and a good product. We value their being a part of our school community.
Because of the shut down of our school... your access to our Royalton Pride apparel has been unavailable for many weeks. But, tomorrow, May 7th and Friday, May 8th... from 9am - 1 pm they will have a rack of a variety of Royalton apparel in front of their store on Main Street in Pierz! These would be great for your moms for Mothers Day... or will help you feel the connection to our school - even from your homes!

Preschool Clarification

Preschool will be closed until we open school again, we are not done for the year. Your students need to take all their belongings home so we can sterilize the areas better. There are no meals provided by the school for pre-K. If you need meals, please contact our secondary social worker Ms. Joann Weir (320-584-4246 or joann.weir@isd485.org). She will work with you to provide meals through our ‚ÄúCare Closet Program‚Äù. This is available for any of our students depending on need.

post_text:
Congrats to our 2020 Section 7A Wrestling Champions!!

They will compete as a team in the Class A State Wrestling Tournament held at Xcel Energy Center on February 27. The Royals defeated Crosby-Ironton, Holdingford, and Aitkin to claim their first section title since 2009 and second in program history. Congrats to Coach Gorecki and his staff and all of our wrestlers! A big thank you to our Royalton-Upsala parents for helping us host the 7A Team Sections this year. Go Royals!

post_text: Mrs. Koenigs' class had fun celebrating the 100th day of school! They completed several writing prompts imagining they were 100 years old, did 100 day math, tested their endurance for 100 seconds at a time, and found some fun facts about the 100 dollar bill. They were also tasked with building the tallest towers they could using 100 toothpicks and 100 cups!

post_text: These #4thGrade #scientists have been working with and learning about rocks and minerals. Lately, they've been doing a "mock rock" experiment. They record observations as they use their senses to learn as much about the mock rocks as possible. They've used tools to break the rocks apart and have also combined them with water to see if they can discover more of the ingredients used to make them. Lastly, they observed the crystals formed after evaporation (in order to determine another ingredient). #FunInFourth
